text: Agdistis notabilis is a moth in the family Pterophoridae. It was first described in 2009 after specimens collected from near Tarrafal, northern Santiago Island, Cape Verde. ==References== Category:Agdistinae Category:Plume moths of Africa Category:Moths of Cape Verde Category:Fauna of Santiago, Cape Verde Category:Moths described in 2009
title: Agdistis notabilis
